#: ../userguides/reference.rst:2 b35f7074558b4dc3af95bfb942daa297
msgid "Reference on using the platform"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:6 ccdd03077ce34056b7ca9ef09fcd4b7f
msgid ""
"This document outlines the requirements for using the Mapflow platform, "
"including supported data formats, preprocessing steps, and model-specific"
" guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:9 fbfe44ba07ee4fbc9c7643fa4ec3eb71
msgid "Requirements for using the platform"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:14 15482e1cfc87429697145080f591483b
msgid "Upload GeoTIFF requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:16 f50fd3e2f6c34a108af53f695d6b8b61
msgid "Please pay attention to the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:18 97b5bb8a20ba4da6b270e6ee07c50cbd
msgid ""
"Images you upload are preprocessed in `Uint8` format. If your image is "
"not of this type and you want to preview it manually before uploading to "
"the Mapflow server, please use our `image preprocessing script "
"<https://github.com/Geoalert/mapflow_data_preprocessor/>`_ or other tools"
" to translate it to the appropriate format;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:19 0af9b610d2064603981271c54406a890
msgid ""
"Your image must be georeferenced in geographic or projected coordinate "
"system, ellipsoid WGS84, it is recommended to use UTM or Web Mercator;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:20 84cad41cad0f41ef81a4cd917a26cee4
msgid ""
"The default limit for file size is ``1 Gb`` for free users. If you have a"
" bigger file – reduce its size or consider switching to the paid plan;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:21 6d269757a47e41e6ad25c53bfb04d929
msgid "Your image should be RGB composite, RGBa or Singleband;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:22 73cbf3a8a5824f14ad7e78e99feb52dc
msgid "Maximum image dimensions: ``65535 px`` per side;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:23 bd7270211f38474fbacfe2c892684cf4
msgid "Pixel size must not exceed ``20 m/px``;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:24 a3d81ba2ca6d4550a5fb054548b4ca68
msgid ""
"Images with a pixel size less than ``10 cm/px`` will be resampled to this"
" resolution;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:25 9d707483b96a4e7881f30018945f9227
msgid "All images within a collection must have the same number of bands;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:26 981c64813a5940feafb6235e81edad51
msgid ""
"Uploaded image will be reprojected and resampled to match the CRS and GSD"
" (pixel size) of other images in collection;"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:27 ba35cec87876458fa14b80d979ca9cce
msgid ""
"Each Mapflow model has its recommendations for the spatial resolution of "
"the input data, see :ref:`Model_requirements` below."
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:29 59980564e9034f84871d833133bbf48f
msgid ""
"In case of non-compliance with any requirements, the system reports an "
"error. If you are using Mapflow Web or Mapflow QGIS plugin, the error "
"messages are shown in the user interface. For more details, see "
":doc:`errors description <../api/error_messages>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:36 6a0f362d3bf3470ab0310ea28af5474a
msgid "Model requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:38 7e6f6a5563084a7b8d00ca40858b8271
msgid ""
"The table below lists model requirements for spatial resolution of the "
"input imagery."
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:40 c0990125eb74427ca759ecd7ba9f8c75
msgid ""
"**\"Required\"** means that the imagery with resolution outside of this "
"range will be rejected from processing and the request will fail."
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:43 9bbb67d8ebb94e798a0ec32c3bd73629
msgid ""
"**\"Recommended\"** means that the model is fit specifically for this "
"spatial resolution. Any images of higher resolution will be downsampled "
"before processing, so it gives no profit to upload higher resolution. "
"Images of lower resolution (if meeting the \"required\" section) will be "
"upsampled, but the results will not be so good as for recommended "
"resolution."
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:48 15160e9aae8643efb2b48770354b91a0
msgid ""
"GSD is specified in `UTM coordinate system "
"<https://proj4.org/en/9.2/operations/projections/utm.html>`_, and may not"
" correspond to what you see as \"pixel size\" if your image's coordinate "
"system differs."
msgstr ""

#: ../userguides/reference.rst:51 428a50fb844b49078588537fe6482d68
msgid ""
"`Learn more <https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Zoom_levels>`_  about "
"zoom and spatial resolution of imagery basemaps."
msgstr ""

